newsitem.title: INDIA: Indian castor prices end lower on profit-taking.
newsitem.headline: Indian castor prices end lower on profit-taking.

text.p: Indian castor December delivery prices ended lower on Thursday at 1,121/1,122 rupees per quintal on profit-taking after opening at 1,126/1,127 rupees, dealers said. September delivery was quoted at 1,090/1,095 rupees.
"Volume in September delivery was negligible ahead of the delivery period," one dealer said.

Arrivals of castorseed in the Gujarat region fell to 7,000-8,000 bags (75 kg each) against 14,000-15,000 bags on Wednesday. Groundnut oil was steady at 431/432 rupees per 10 kg on limited inflows of 40-50 tonnes. In Rajkot spot oil rose by five rupees to 665/670 rupees per 15 kg.
